		p In this Privacy Policy we will explain how we collect, use, store, and share your personal information and other data (collectively referred to “data” hereafter) when you are using or creating an account on the Bisring Website. We may change or update this policy and any changes or updates to this policy will come into effect when it is posted on our website. Your continued use of the Website means that you acknowledge any updates and accept them. If you do not agree with this policy or with any changes to the policy please discontinue your use and email us to voice your concerns.
		p When you create an account on our Website, engage with us by email or social media, subscribe to our emails or call inquiring something, different types of data is being collected. When you become a Bisringer, certain data is collected such as: Name, Home Address, Phone Number, Email Address and Credit Card information. This data is used to verify your identity when you are creating an account on our Website, communicate with you regarding your engagement with our Website, send promotional or marketing content, for billing purposes (third party provider [■]), allow you to interact with other Bisringers, to receive notifications, to help us improve our Website, create reports based on your engagement with the Website, to calculate the most used areas of our Website, to see where Bisringers are located, gather data about Bisringer postings,  and track platform usage, violations, fraud, or illegal activities.
		p Bisring will not make public outside of our Website any of your personal information such as your name, phone number, email address, home address, credit card information without your express written consent. Your credit card information is stored by [■] Stripe which is an independent third party and will in no way be released to anyone by Bisring. We are not responsible for what happens to or what our third party service providers do with your data. By interacting with our third party service providers you are acknowledging that they may collect your data as well which Bisring is not responsible for. We ask that you do not disclose any of your personal information unless you are explicitly asked by Bisring when creating a profile or processing a transaction. 
		p Bisring follows the laws of the Province of Ontario and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein. By using our Website you agree that your collected data may pass through different geographic areas in which Bisring operates in. As a result, this information may be subject to access requests from governments, courts, regulatory agencies, security authorities or law enforcement in those jurisdictions according to the laws in those jurisdictions.
		p We may use your location for the purpose of localizing search results. We may also collect information about your device type and operating systems. Our third party providers may automatically obtain information when you visit our Website, including cookies, web beacons and other technologies. Cookies are small files which are stored on your computer. They are designed to hold a small amount of data specific to a particular website, and can be accessed either by the web server or your computer.
		p If you register as a Bisringer, we may share your business data with other Bisringers and Users. We may also share your profile data with business partners or associates, as needed, with service providers who may work on our behalf, such as cloud storage providers, and other third party service providers that provide features or functionalities which we integrate into our Website, such as payment processors, with  our legal counsel, accountants, auditors or other advisors or as required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena or other legal process, or to comply with government reporting obligations. 
		p When we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary (a) to protect our rights, the integrity of the Website, or your safety or the safety of other Bisringers, or (b) to detect, prevent, or respond to theft or fraud, violations of law or our policies or Terms and Conditions of Use. 
		p The Website does have third party service providers such as but not limited to payment processing, data storage, analytics, and hosting. These providers may collect and store your data, your IP address of the device you are using to connect with the Website. It is also possible that these providers send a cookie to ensure all features and services are working properly and as expected. Any interactions with these third party service providers from our Website are governed by the policies of the companies that provide the service or function. 
		p The Website is not intended for anyone under the age of eighteen (18) years old and we do not target the Website to people under age. If an underage person does wish to engage with our platform it must be accompanied by a parent or guardian by using their credit card. By doing so the parent or guardian assumes all responsibility and liability for the underage Bisringer. If you know an underage user has created an account on the platform without the permission or consent of a parent or guardian please email us.
		p By creating an account on the Website and entering your personal information, you acknowledge that some of this will be made public for any of our Bisringers to view or a person browsing the Website. The only information that will be made public is your business contact information. 
		p Any data that you have entered on the Website such as your personal information may be changed at any time by logging into your account and editing your profile. For your protection and the protection of our Bisringers you may be subject to review as we have to verify the edited information. If you wish to close your account with Bisring and then have us clear any of your personal data from our system as best as we can, please email us to do so.
		p We have strived to put into place reasonable security measures in an effort to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, destruction, or alteration while it is under our control. However, no method of transmission over the Internet, and no method of storing information can be 100% secure. As a result, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your transmissions to us and of your personal data that we store. We are not responsible for any unauthorized disclosure of personal or other data caused by any of our third party providers. Your account data is accessible online through the use of your private password. To protect the confidentiality of your personal data, you must keep your password confidential and not disclose it to any other person. You are responsible for all uses of our Website by any person using your password or your account. Please advise us immediately if you believe your password has been compromised. We are not responsible for your failure to comply with this clause, or for any delay in shutting down your account after you have reported a breach of security to us.
